# Research Paper Intelligence System

## Overview

Research Paper Intelligence System is an AI-powered research assistant that helps users discover, analyze, and understand machine learning research papers through semantic search and Large Language Models (LLMs).

The system indexes thousands of research papers by generating dense vector embeddings and storing them in a FAISS vector database. Instead of relying on traditional keyword matching, it performs semantic retrieval to identify the most relevant papers for a given user query.

Beyond retrieval, the system automatically summarizes research papers, extracts important keywords, generates structured research profiles using Large Language Models, and provides an intelligent interface for exploring academic literature.

---

## Features

* Semantic Search using dense vector embeddings
* Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline
* FAISS Vector Database for efficient similarity search
* Research paper summarization using BART
* Automatic keyword extraction using KeyBERT
* AI-generated research paper profiling
* Similarity-based paper ranking
* LangChain tools and agents integration
* LLM-powered research assistant
* Intelligent recommendation of related research papers

